    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap 10. 1881</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental"><hi rend="italic">To R. Cooke Esq</hi></seg>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Please to read the accompanying note to Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Clowes<ref target="#foot.f1"/>   The book will consist of 7 chapters, and will extend, as I have roughly computed to between 260 and 280 pp<ref target="#foot.f2"/>   I do not care whether it is published by you on commission or on our former terms of <formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></formula> profits   I cannot even conjecture whether 200 or 2000 copies will be sold. Therefore M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray must form his own judgment; and I think that he or your reader can judge to a certain extent by reading the short introduction and the table of contents to each chapter.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> But unless M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray can make up his mind in a day, I wish to publish on commission, so that no time may be lost before the M.S. is in Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Clowes’ hands. You will see in my note to them why I am in such a hurry.</p>
<p>Please to let me hear what you decide, and believe me | my dear Sir, | Yours sincerely | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The note to CD’s printer, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_979.xml">William Clowes &amp; Sons</ref>, has not been found.</note> 
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The seven chapters, the introduction, and the index of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref> came to a total of 326 pages.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3463.xml">John Murray</ref> (1808–92) was CD’s publisher.</note>
        </div>
    
